--- VERDICT for Phase 8c ---
(a) Full 10-input primary NCDVI: NOT transportable. All four sb318 advice
    variables (b,c,d,e) absent from BDHS 2022 across PR, HR, IR. Confirmed.
(b) 6-input sensitivity NCDVI (occupation + BMI + cook_fuel + water_source +
    toilet_type + crowding): TRANSPORTABLE WITH ENGINEERING.
    - 4 structural inputs (cook_fuel, water_source, toilet_type, crowding):
      directly available in BDPR81 (one row per household member).
    - BMI: must be computed from BDHR81 wide anthropometry blocks (ha2_k/ha3_k
      for women, hb2_k/hb3_k for men) joined back to PR via household roster slot.
    - occupation: only available in BDIR81 (women's IR). Sample reduces to women.
(c) Outcome (HTN) is partially constructable from BDPR81 wbp1-wbp3 + mbp1-mbp3.
    BP medication and glucose for diabetic confounder need a deeper file search.

